<Layout
	title="About Siddharth"
	description="WG21 member and systems engineer focusing on C++ and build infrastructure."
	pubDate={new Date('March 04 2026')}
>
	<p>
		I am a systems engineer and a member of <strong>WG21</strong>, the ISO C++ Standards Committee. My work primarily revolves around performance-critical systems, compiler internals, and the infrastructure that enables large-scale C++ development.
	</p>

	<h2>Technical Focus</h2>
	<p>
		My primary interest is in reducing the friction of building and maintaining modern C++. This involves:
	</p>
	<ul>
		<li><strong>Standardization:</strong> Contributing to the design and evolution of the C++ language.</li>
		<li><strong>Build Infrastructure:</strong> Developing <em>Catalyst</em>, an AST-informed build system designed to handle the complexities of modern C++ dependency graphs and modules.</li>
		<li><strong>Observability:</strong> Improving how we reason about and monitor systems-level software.</li>
	</ul>

	<h2>Why this blog?</h2>
	<p>
		The C++ standardization process can often feel opaque to the broader community. I aim to provide insider design rationale, explain the technical trade-offs behind new features, and share my experiences building systems-level tooling from the ground up.
	</p>

	<p>
		You can find me on <a href="https://github.com">GitHub</a> or follow my work here.
	</p>
</Layout>
